{"type":"message","id":"6451d2b9","parentId":"dc5eff76","timestamp":"2026-04-19T03:32:04.879Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"4 agents spawned successfully. Now let me also spawn product-marketing-context and stitch-design in parallel. Actually, let me also spawn product-marketing-context for the brand voice piece.\n\nAlso, I should spawn senior-frontend to start scaffolding the project (T8) as soon as senior-architect finishes T1. But T8 depends on T1, so I should wait for T1 to complete first. However, I can spawn senior-frontend with a conditional task that waits for T1.\n\nActually, looking at the task dependency more carefully:\n- T1 → T8 → T9 → T10 → T11\n- T3 → T4\n\n\nI could try running T8 and T11 in parallel since they don't depend on each other, but T8 needs the architecture file from T1. So I'll wait for T1 to complete before starting T8. Let me go ahead and spawn product-marketing-context now since it doesn't have dependencies.","thinkingSignature":"3108929aba023c35e767c83a3e4f3d445e629dea640c50d75de2814144f585e7"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hia9xhg3upwg_1","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"You are product-marketing-context. Define the brand voice, ICP (Ideal Customer Profile), and positioning for the AHV Tech Knowledge Hub.\n\nProject location: /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-knowledge-hub/\n\nRead the OpenSpec first: /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-knowledge-hub/openspec/changes/tech-blog/proposal.md\n\nYour task (T7): Brand voice, ICP, and market positioning.\n\nDeliverables — write to /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-knowledge-hub/openspec/changes/tech-blog/brand-voice.md:\n\n1. **Brand Identity**:\n   - Brand name: \"AHV Tech Hub\" or alternative suggestions\n   - Tagline (Vietnamese, catchy, memorable)\n   - Mission statement\n   - Value proposition\n\n2. **Tone of Voice**:\n   - How the blog speaks (friendly, authoritative, encouraging, etc.)\n   - Do's and Don'ts for content writers\n   - Example sentences in Vietnamese across different contexts\n\n3. **Ideal Customer Profile (ICP)**:\n   - Primary persona: Student/beginner (18-25yo, Vietnamese, learning programming)\n   - Secondary persona: Career switcher (25-35yo, learning CS fundamentals)\n   - Pain points: Overwhelmed by English resources, need structured Vietnamese content\n   - Where they find content: Google, YouTube, Facebook groups, Reddit\n\n4. **Competitive Positioning**:\n   - Who are the competitors (techtalk.vn, viblo.asia, kipalog.com, etc.)\n   - Differentiation: What's unique vs competitors\n   - SWOT analysis\n\n5. **Content Positioning**:\n   - How articles should feel (like a smart friend explaining)\n   - Code example standards (real code, not toy examples)\n   - Difficulty calibration (gradual difficulty increase)\n   - Why Vietnamese-first content matters\n\nWrite the file now. Reply briefly when done.","label":"ahv-knowledge-hub:product-marketing-context","runtime":"subagent","agentId":"product-marketing-context","mode":"run"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":766,"output":696,"cacheRead":33209,"cacheWrite":2984,"totalTokens":37655,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776569486364,"responseId":"06337f8f1925efaafa554f2e4f957dfd"}}
