{"type":"message","id":"40ef6006","parentId":"226b878a","timestamp":"2026-04-19T03:43:20.677Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Now let me verify the changes look good and then scaffold the Next.js project. But wait - I should also update the MEMORY.md to reflect the new project name and group name.\n\nLet me also try to spawn a senior-frontend agent with the DEV model to see if it works. But first, let me scaffold the project directly since agents are timing out.\n\nActually, let me think about the approach. The Lead wants me to:\n1. Check model usage and fix if wrong → Already confirmed agents use TroLy\n2. Create GitLab group → Need Lead to do manually\n3. Continue Phase 2\n\nFor Phase 2 (scaffold Next.js), I can either:\n\n\n- Do it directly (write files myself) - this works but the project won't be in GitLab yet\n- Spawn senior-frontend with model override\n\nSince the model provider is unstable with timeouts, I'll write the core Next.js project files directly while Lead creates the GitLab group. Once that's done, we can connect everything. This is the fastest path forward right now.\n\nI'll set up the package.json with all dependencies, configure TypeScript and Tailwind, establish the Next.js app structure, add all the core components and pages, configure shadcn/ui, set up the MDX pipeline, and add SEO utilities.","thinkingSignature":"5b1e0252209149c6abc828337cf9b43750efb93696748a2cf4db4ddf9a8374e7"},{"type":"text","text":"Rename xong ✅. Giờ scaffold Next.js project trực tiếp (bỏ qua model vì provider đang 500). GitLab group Lead tạo riêng.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_tx64t4kanllq_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub/package.json","content":"{\n  \"name\": \"maiy-tech-hub\",\n  \"version\": \"0.1.0\",\n  \"private\": true,\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"dev\": \"next dev\",\n    \"build\": \"next build\",\n    \"start\": \"next start\",\n    \"