{"type":"message","id":"17eca454","parentId":"e0bc0537","timestamp":"2026-04-19T04:15:09.110Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lead is pointing out several critical issues:\n\n1. **Git workflow violations**: I pushed directly to `develop` without creating a feature branch. This violates the mandatory git workflow in MEMORY.md.\n2. **Repo structure**: FE and BE are in the same repo — Lead wants to split them into separate repos.\n3. **OpenClaw agent setup files** were pushed to the maiy-tech-hub repo (they shouldn't be there).\n4. **MAIY Tech Hub** should be a separate repo from the OpenClaw ecosystem repo.\n\nThe correct workflow should be:\n1. Checkout `develop`, pull latest\n2. Create feature branch from `develop`\n\n\n3. Work on the feature branch\n4. Push feature branch\n5. Create MR → target `develop`\n\nFor maiy-tech-hub, Lead wants FE and BE in separate repos:\n- `maiy/maiy-tech-hub` (FE - Next.js)\n- `maiy/maiy-tech-hub-be` (BE - if needed, but for MAIY it's mostly a FE project with MDX content)\n\nActually, MAIY Tech Hub is primarily a Next.js frontend project with MDX content and Socket.IO server. The Socket.IO server could be embedded in Next.js or split out.\n\nBut wait — I pushed setup files into the maiy-tech-hub repo by accident, when they should only live in the v4-ecosystem-review workspace. I need to undo those commits from the maiy repo, clean up the setup files, and establish the proper git workflow going forward. I need to undo those commits from the maiy repo since they contain OpenClaw setup files that shouldn't be there. I'll use git revert to back them out, then establish the proper feature branch workflow going forward—checking out develop, pulling the latest changes, creating a new feature branch, making updates, pushing it up, and opening a merge request. I should also clarify with the Lead how to handle the repository structure since MAIY is primarily a frontend Next.js project with MDX content rather than a full-stack application.\n\nThe key decision is whether to keep the Socket.IO server embedded in Next.js or split it out—most MAIY Tech Hub features are frontend-focused (blog, music player, study rooms with YouTube embeds), so I could either integrate the server into the Next.js app for simplicity or keep it as a separate service. I also need to revert the commits that accidentally included setup files from the wrong repository.","thinkingSignature":"fcd588a777b5aa080e83029d73214618ecfffdae2f6fb15da6bb3740071ae95d"},{"type":"text","text":"Lead đúng — mình đã vi phạm git workflow. Xin lỗi. Mình sẽ:\n\n1. **Revert các commits** sai trên maiy-hub (vì push thẳng lên develop + lẫn setup files)\n2. **Sửa git workflow đúng**: feature branch → MR → merge\n3. **Chia FE/BE** thành 2 repos nếu cần\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hkwmly209nuy_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub && git log --oneline maiy/develop -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":370,"output":667,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":131109,"totalTokens":132146,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776572084562,"responseId":"063389b746c26bd47deab575415af209"}}
