{"type":"message","id":"dad22c19","parentId":"0df15d93","timestamp":"2026-04-19T04:17:06.434Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Ah, the entire v4-ecosystem-review IS a git repo. So when I ran git checkout develop and git reset --soft, it was operating on the entire workspace, not just maiy-tech-hub. The maiy-tech-hub folder doesn't have its own .git - it's part of the parent git repo.\n\nThis explains the mess. Let me:1. Unstage everything from the parent git repo\n2. Check what's actually on the maiy-hub remote (what was pushed after reset)3. Work properly within this structure\n\nFor maiy-tech-hub to be pushed to maiy-hub GitLab, I need to handle it as a subdirectory of the workspace repo. This is the issue - the workspace IS a monorepo of agents, and pushing subdirectories to separate remotes is complex.\n\n\nI need to untangle this - the workspace has its own remote pointing to ahv-dtlx/v4-ecosystem-review, while maiy-tech-hub was supposed to go to a separate maiy-hub/maiy-tech-hub repo. The git history is showing all the workspace files mixed together, so I should reset everything and then figure out how to properly extract just the maiy-tech-hub content for the maiy-hub remote.\n\nActually, I'm realizing the better approach is to unstage those workspace changes, keep the actual MAIY Tech Hub files I need, and commit those separately to maiy-hub, while committing the workspace files back to the original v4-ecosystem-review repo instead. The real issue is that all these commits got mixed together when I was working across both repositories.","thinkingSignature":"d11b472108047ba3936af64532867cf7b16ed27053ba199d816f6f6425c45ea0"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_pucvbi95uigi_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review && git checkout . && git status --short | grep \"^.M\" | grep -v \"maiy-tech-hub\" | head -20 && echo \"---\" && ls /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-