{"type":"compaction","id":"96e0b893","parentId":"5febc07a","timestamp":"2026-04-19T04:38:51.389Z","summary":"## Goal\nBuild \"MAIY Tech Hub\" — a modern IT knowledge blog with Next.js 14, featuring: blog articles (CTDL, AI, Web Dev, DevOps, CS Fundamentals), music relaxation zone, live study rooms with Pomodoro timer, SEO-optimized content in Vietnamese.\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Project must be under GitLab group `maiy-hub` (already created by Lead)\n- Project name: \"MAIY Tech Hub\" (renamed from \"AHV Tech Knowledge Hub\")\n- Model: `ahvholding/AHV-Holding-DEV` (Lead changed from TroLy to DEV)\n- Git workflow: **Feature branch → MR → Merge to develop** (Lead explicitly called out violations)\n- No pushing directly to `develop`\n- FE and BE should be separate repos\n- OpenClaw agent setup files must NOT be pushed to project repos\n- After running dev server in parallel for Lead review, continue Phase 4\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Phase 1 Planning: 7 OpenSpec docs written (proposal, architecture, content-strategy, seo-strategy, wireframes, brand-voice, tasks) in `maiy-tech-hub/openspec/changes/tech-blog/`\n- [x] Phase 2 Scaffold: Full Next.js 14 project created at `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub/`\n- [x] Pages built: Home, Articles listing, Article detail, Music, Study, Search\n- [x] SEO: sitemap.ts, robots.ts, JSON-LD ArticleSchema, breadcrumbs\n- [x] Design: dark/light mode, Tailwind CSS, responsive\n- [x] Music zone: Mood selector, YouTube embeds, persistent mini-player\n- [x] Study room: Pomodoro timer, room create/join, participant list, ambient sounds\n- [x] Phase 3: shadcn/ui components (button, card, badge, input, dialog, sheet, avatar, separator)\n- [x] Phase 3: Socket.IO server (`server/server.ts`), `/api/rooms` route, `hooks/use-socket.ts`, `hooks/use-pomodoro.ts`\n- [x] Phase 3: 8 MDX sample articles (binary-search, dynamic-programming, linear-regression-python, neural-network-from-scratch, nextjs-app-router, docker-compose, stack-heap-memory, github-actions-ci-cd)\n- [x] Model switched to DEV in `/root/.openclaw/openclaw2.json` (36 instances updated)\n- [x] GitLab repo `maiy-hub/maiy-tech-hub` created and pushed to (via HTTPS with token)\n- [x] Both `main` and `develop` branches pushed\n- [x] Build verified: 12/12 static pages ✅, Lint: no warnings ✅\n- [x] DEV model tested and working ✅\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Running `yarn dev` for Lead to review (Lead requested this in last message)\n- [ ] Fixing git workflow violations on `maiy-hub/maiy-tech-hub`\n- [ ] Confirming FE/BE repo split strategy\n- [ ] Phase 4 (Playwright E2E + SEO audit)\n\n### Blocked\n- Git history on `maiy-hub/maiy-tech-hub` has violations: commits pushed directly to `develop` instead of feature branches; commits from v4-ecosystem-review accidentally merged in\n- OpenClaw agent setup files were pushed to maiy-hub repo — need to clean\n- Lead requested parallel `yarn dev` + Phase 4 but hasn't confirmed FE/BE split plan yet\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Tech stack**: Next.js 14 App Router + TypeScript + Tailwind + shadcn/ui + MDX + Socket.IO + Vercel\n- **Content approach**: MDX files in `content/articles/` with frontmatter (title, excerpt, category, tags, hero, author, date)\n- **Music strategy**: YouTube/Spotify embed (no self-hosted audio)\n- **Live Study**: Socket.IO on same Next.js server (custom server.ts)\n- **Dev model**: `ahvholding/AHV-Holding-DEV` as primary (after Lead's instruction)\n- **TroLy/DEV both failing with HTTP 500**: Provider-side issue; DEV worked for subsequent agents but shadcn-expert still got 500 (though it completed work anyway)\n- **GitLab push**: Used HTTPS with token `glpat-c_N4qQVxbcktRro-S5rdwGM6MQpvOjEKdTpoZDBsYg8` after SSH key was denied\n\n## Next Steps\n1. **Immediate**: Start `yarn dev` server so Lead can review the live app\n2. **Git fix**: Revert commits `0bba3fd` and `3efcb9a` on maiy-hub develop; start proper feature branch workflow\n3. **Confirm with Lead**: Should MAIY Tech Hub be FE-only or FE+BE split across two repos?\n4. **Proper Phase 4 git workflow**: Create `feat/playwright-e2e` branch → write tests → push → create MR\n5. **Proper Phase 4 execution**: Playwright E2E tests (home, article, music, study flows) + seo-audit\n\n## Critical Context\n- **GitLab repo**: `https://gitlab.com/maiy-hub/maiy-tech-hub`\n- **Workspace path**: `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub/`\n- **OpenSpec path**: `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub/openspec/changes/tech-blog/`\n- **Current Git history on maiy-hub develop** (from newest to oldest):\n  - `0bba3fd` — feat(maiy): shadcn/ui, Socket.IO server, 5 MDX articles, hooks (pushed directly to develop ❌)\n  - `3efcb9a` — Merge branch 'main' (lẫn commit từ v4-ecosystem-review ❌)\n  - `c43dc73` — Initial commit (README.md only — clean)\n- **MAIY Tech Hub Git remote (HTTPS)**: `https://khuowgn:[token]@gitlab.com/maiy-hub/maiy-tech-hub.git`\n- **v4-ecosystem-review remote (SSH — broken)**: `git@gitlab.com:ahv-dtlx/v4-ecosystem-review.git`\n- **Socket.IO server file**: `server/server.ts` (custom server, uses `tsx` to run)\n- **Package.json dev script**: `yarn dev` (standard Next.js); `yarn server` (Socket.IO custom server)\n- **8 articles** across 5 categories: ctdl (2), ai (2), web-dev (2), cs-fundamentals (1), devops (1)\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Original Request\nLead chose option A to fix bad git commits in the maiy-tech-hub project - revert to correct state, establish proper feature branch workflow, and run the project for review.\n\n## Early Progress\n- Discovered the entire v4-ecosystem-review workspace IS a git repo (monorepo for 34 agents), causing maiy-tech-hub commits to get mixed with workspace files\n- Re-initialized maiy-tech-hub as a completely independent git repo, separate from the workspace\n- Set up remote 'maiy' with HTTPS authentication (SSH was denied)\n- Successfully fetched from maiy-hub/maiy-tech-hub - both main and develop branches are available\n- Remote develop branch is reset to c43dc73 (Initial commit with README)\n- Checked local directory contents - project files exist (.eslintrc.json, .gitignore, .next, README.md, SPEC.md, app/)\n\n## Context for Suffix\n- maiy-tech-hub is now an independent git repo (isolated from v4-ecosystem-review workspace)\n- Remote 'maiy' configured with HTTPS for pushing/fetching\n- Project structure intact after reset\n- Next steps: set up proper branch workflow and add the full project files\n\n<read-files>\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/skills/master-orchestrator/SKILL.md\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/prompt-optimizer/SKILL.md\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/prompt-optimizer/skills/prompt-optimizer/SKILL.md\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\n/root/.openclaw/openclaw2.json\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecospace-review/master-orchestrator/memory/2026-04-19.md\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-knowledge-hub/openspec/changes/tech-blog/architecture.md\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-knowledge-hub/openspec/changes/tech-blog/brand-voice.md\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-knowledge-hub/openspec/changes/tech-blog/content-strategy.md\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-knowledge-hub/openspec/changes/tech-blog/proposal.md\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-knowledge-hub/openspec/changes/tech-blog/seo-strategy.md\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-knowledge-hub/openspec/changes/tech-blog/tasks.md\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-knowledge-hub/openspec/changes/tech-blog/wireframes.md\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub/.eslintrc.json\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub/.gitignore\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub/README.md\n/root/.openclaw/workspac