{"type":"message","id":"d63594c5","parentId":"543d3a5b","timestamp":"2026-04-19T04:46:09.396Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to update the article page to use the MDXContent component. Let me also update the lib/content.ts to use serialize from next-mdx-remote/serialize.\n\nActually, the issue is that `next-mdx-remote/serialize` is for pages, and for App Router we should use `next-mdx-remote/rsc` which is the RSC-compatible version. Let me check.\n\nLooking at next-mdx-remote docs for App Router:\n- `next-mdx-remote/rsc` — for server components (App Router)\n- `next-mdx-remote` — for pages (Pages Router)\n\n\n- Since we're using App Router, I need to switch to `next-mdx-remote/rsc` and update both the content library and article page accordingly.","thinkingSignature":"16fdd2286036fd464809c0b664d794b88161ba6e23eeb8a09d1ed69f59f8a351"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wj0necqpg9js_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub && node -e \"const r = require('next-mdx-remote/rsc'); console.log('RSC available')\" 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":104,"output":236,"cacheRead":64381,"cacheWrite":1791,"totalTokens":66512,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776573961586,"responseId":"0633910ab5a2322f3e88355180e609f1"}}
