{"type":"message","id":"b414339c","parentId":"62619af1","timestamp":"2026-04-19T05:11:28.535Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Build is running. While waiting, let me also create the Socket.IO server properly for real-time study rooms. I need to make sure the server can run properly.","thinkingSignature":"cb07f9e77db34896c9baea90b6d50c8030974c794ea112843453b27edcdcbc06"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_p7m3jpwsmes3_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub/server/server.ts"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":108,"output":81,"cacheRead":119821,"cacheWrite":904,"totalTokens":120914,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776575483246,"responseId":"063396fcd55f00ae912be1d900f9bc6a"}}
{"type":"message","id":"bfb0f0aa","parentId":"b414339c","timestamp":"2026-04-19T05:11:28.613Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_p7m3jpwsmes3_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import { createServer } from 'http'\nimport { parse } from 'url'\nimport next from 'next'\nimport { Server as SocketIOServer } from 'socket.io'\n\nconst dev = process.env.NODE_ENV !== 'production'\nconst app = next({ dev })\nconst handle = app.getRequestHandler()\n\napp.prepare().then(() => {\n  const httpServer = createServer((req, res) => {\n    const parsedUrl = parse(req.url!, true)\n    handle(req, res, parsedUrl)\n  })\n\n  const io = new SocketIOServer(httpServer, {\n    cors: {\n      origin: process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL || 'http://localhost:3000',\n      methods: ['GET', 'POST'],\n    },\n  })\n\n  // Socket.IO event handlers\n  io.on('connection', (socket) => {\n    console.log(`User connected: ${socket.id}`)\n\n    // Join study room\n    socket.on('join-room', ({ roomId, username }: { roomId: string; username: string }) => {\n      socket.join(roomId)\n      const room = io.sockets.adapter.rooms.get(roomId)\n      const count = room?.size ?? 0\n      io.to(roomId).emit('user-joined', { username, id: socket.id, count })\n      socket.data.username = username\n      socket.data.roomId = roomId\n      console.log(`${username} joined room ${roomId} (${count} users)`)\n    })\n\n    // Leave room\n    socket.on('leave-room', ({ roomId, username }: { roomId: string; username: string }) => {\n      socket.leave(roomId)\n      const room = io.sockets.adapter.rooms.get(roomId)\n      const count = room?.size ?? 0\n      io.to(roomId).emit('user-left', { username, id: socket.id, count })\n      console.log(`${username} left room ${roomId} (${count} users)`)\n    })\n\n    // Pomodoro sync\n    socket.on('pomodoro-tick', ({ roomId, timeLeft, phase, sessionCount }: any) => {\n      socket.to(roomId).emit('pomodoro-sync', { timeLeft, phase, sessionCount })\n    })\n\n    // Disconnect\n    socket.on('disconnect', () => {\n      if (socket.data.roomId && socket.data.username) {\n        const { roomId, username } = socket.data\n        socket.leave(roomId)\n        const room = io.sockets.adapter.rooms.get(roomId)\n        const count = room?.size ?? 0\n        io.to(roomId).emit('user-left', { username, id: socket.id, count })\n      }\n      console.log(`User disconnected: ${socket.id}`)\n    })\n  })\n\n  const port = process.env.PORT || 3000\n  httpServer.listen(port, () => {\n    console.log(`> Ready on http://localhost:${port}`)\n  })\n})\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776575488586}}
{"type":"message","id":"8120eb9c","parentId":"bfb0f0aa","timestamp":"2026-04-19T05:11:36.471Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The Socket.IO server is already well-structured. The issue is that in production, we can't run both Next.js and Socket.IO on the same port easily. For a proper setup, we'd either need:\n1. A separate Socket.IO server on a different port\n2. Use a custom server with Socket.IO integrated (which is what we have)\n\nThe current `server/server.ts` integrates Socket.IO with Next.js custom server. For development, this works. For production on Vercel, we'd need a different approach.\n\nFor now, let me improve the Study page to use the Socket.IO client properly and make the real-time features work. The hooks already exist (`use-socket.ts` and `use-pomodoro.ts`). \n\nI'm realizing the study page has local state management for Pomodoro and room joining, but it's not actually connected to the Socket.IO server. I need to wire up the `use-socket.ts` and `use-pomodoro.ts` hooks so the study page can communicate with the Socket.IO server for real-time synchronization across clients.","thinkingSignature":"c6a44edf5e1969599650a58d9e6a98bd8050018957f40239cea44d3f9c444389"},{"type":"text","text":"Socket.IO server đã có — giờ cải thiện study page kết nối real-time:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xf9gvk6om5oy_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub/hooks/use-socket.ts"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":693,"output":290,"cacheRead":120603,"cacheWrite":249,"totalTokens":121835,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776575488622,"responseId":"0633970297caabd60dc4dcafe08c3299"}}
{"type":"message","id":"57dfc1f1","parentId":"8120eb9c","timestamp":"2026-04-19T05:11:36.536Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_xf9gvk6om5oy_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"'use client'\n\nimport { useEffect, useRef, useState, useCallback } from 'react'\nimport { io, Socket } from 'socket.io-client'\n\nexport function useSocket() {\n  const socketRef = useRef<Socket | null>(null)\n  const [isConnected, setIsConnected] = useState(false)\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (!socketRef.current) {\n      socketRef.current = io(process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL || '', {\n        path: '/api/socket',\n        transports: ['websocket', 'polling'],\n      })\n\n      socketRef.current.on('connect', () => {\n        setIsConnected(true)\n        console.log('Socket connected')\n      })\n\n      socketRef.current.on('disconnect', () => {\n        setIsConnected(false)\n        console.log('Socket disconnected')\n      })\n    }\n\n    return () => {\n      socketRef.current?.disconnect()\n    }\n  }, [])\n\n  return { socket: socketRef.current, isConnected }\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776575496512}}
{"type":"message","id":"723b4c9d","parentId":"57dfc1f1","timestamp":"2026-04-19T05:11:46.711Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The useSocket hook tries to connect to `NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL` at path `/api/socket`. But our Socket.IO server uses the default path `/socket.io`. Let me fix this and also make the study page actually use the socket.\n\nFor the custom server approach, the Socket.IO server attaches to the same HTTP server as Next.js, so the path would be `/socket.io` (default). Let me update the hook.","thinkingSignature":"658e53704eeedaa3948149a5add2f0343d8f4be5de53e899f89ccdc84c044b18"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_p5fsx77ekqs5_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub/hooks/use-socket.ts","content":"'use client'\n\nimport { useEffect, useRef, useState, useCallback } from 'react'\nimport { io, Socket } from 'socket.io-client'\n\nconst SOCKET_URL = process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL || 'http://localhost:3000'\n\nexport function useSocket() {\n  const socketRef = useRef<Socket | null>(null)\n  const [isConnected, setIsConnected] = useState(false)\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (socketRef.current) return\n\n    socketRef.current = io(SOCKET_URL, {\n      transports: ['websocket', 'polling'],\n      reconnection: true,\n      reconnectionAttempts: 5,\n      reconnectionDelay: 1000,\n    })\n\n    socketRef.current.on('connect', () => {\n      setIsConnected(true)\n    })\n\n    socketRef.current.on('disconnect', () => {\n      setIsConnected(false)\n    })\n\n    socketRef.current.on('connect_error', (err) => {\n      console.warn('Socket connection error:', err.message)\n      setIsConnected(false)\n    })\n\n    return () => {\n      socketRef.current?.disconnect()\n      socketRef.current = null\n    }\n  }, [])\n\n  const joinRoom = useCallback((roomId: string, username: string) => {\n    socketRef.current?.emit('join-room', { roomId, username })\n  }, [])\n\n  const leaveRoom = useCallback((roomId: string, username: string) => {\n    socketRef.current?.emit('leave-room', { roomId, username })\n  }, [])\n\n  const syncPomodoro = useCallback(\n    (roomId: string, timeLeft: number, phase: string, sessionCount: number) => {\n      socketRef.current?.emit('pomodoro-tick', { roomId, timeLeft, phase, sessionCount })\n    },\n    []\n  )\n\n  return { socket: socketRef.current, isConnected, joinRoom, leaveRoom, syncPomodoro }\n}\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":283,"output":563,"cacheRead":120766,"cacheWrite":1007,"totalTokens":122619,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776575496546,"responseId":"0633970a00e75f2a19144c10205145a2"}}
