{"type":"message","id":"c4467778","parentId":"4bec687f","timestamp":"2026-04-19T05:30:35.092Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lead wants me to keep going without asking. Let me continue adding features to push from 95% to 100%. Let me think about what would make this a truly impressive product:\n\n1. **Comments system** - using localStorage for MVP (no backend needed), then real comments later\n2. **Table of contents with active heading highlighting** - already have TOC, but can improve\n3. **Better article cards with hover preview**\n4. **Reading time estimates with actual word count**\n5. **Tags page** - browse all tags\n6. **Related articles by tags** - not just same category\n7. **Article reading progress persistence** - save where you left off\n\n\n8. **Dark/light mode with smooth transition**\n9. **Better SEO** - canonical URLs, Twitter cards\n10. **Contact page** \n11. **Privacy policy page**\n12. **Better 404 page with suggestions**\n13. **Reading history** - recently read articles\n14. **Popular articles** - based on reading time\n15. **Quick links / bookmarks**\n16. **Article series** - group articles into series\n17. **Code syntax highlighting** - using shiki or highlight.js\n18. **Better mobile experience** - swipe between articles\n19. **Reading mode** - distraction-free reading\n20. **Export article as PDF**\n\nI'll tackle these in order of impact, focusing on features that work without external services first. For the reading progress feature, I'll use localStorage to persist where users left off in an article, so they can pick up right where they stopped. On the SEO side, I need to add canonical URLs and Twitter card meta tags to improve discoverability. The code highlighting can leverage shiki which is already integrated with the markdown processor. I'm going to focus on the features that have the most impact and don't require external services. I'll start with a contact page, improve the 404 experience with article suggestions, add proper syntax highlighting for code blocks, and create a tags browsing page. These are all self-contained and will round out the experience nicely.","thinkingSignature":"d44f21b5dec4a03b5f9063a4cdaed59f21156983e1e4cd0b017faf3f83488728"},{"type":"text","text":"Tiếp tục đẩy lên 100%. Tạo branch mới:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_k97ydd7plj1n_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub && git checkout -b feat/100-percent && echo \"On feat/100-percent\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":171,"output":509,"cacheRead":143131,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":143811,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776576614818,"responseId":"06339b690834a150e8f296f27f922eb7"}}
