{"type":"message","id":"348c712d","parentId":"15d08b83","timestamp":"2026-04-19T07:16:25.067Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The files exist! Let me check what `getAllSlugs` returns. Let me look at the `getAllSlugs` function in lib/content.ts. It reads from CONTENT_DIR which is `path.join(process.cwd(), 'content', 'articles')`. This should work since the cwd would be the project root.\n\nWait, let me check if the slug in the URL matches the filename. The directory structure is `content/articles/ctdl/binary-search.mdx`, but the code looks for `content/articles/binary-search.mdx` at the top level. The `getArticleFiles` function reads from CONTENT_DIR which should contain subdirectories.","thinkingSignature":"081339ca788cf8a4909a7c500028312d0c16e61c256f944e700a3f28ea430b06"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_iqwfjv22k61n_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"node -e \"\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst path = require('path');\nconst matter = require('gray-matter');\nconst CONTENT_DIR = path.join(process.cwd(), 'content', 'articles');\nconst files = fs.readdirSync(CONTENT_DIR);\nconsole.log('Files at top level:', files);\nconst allFiles = [];\nfiles.forEach(f => {\n  const fullPath = path.join(CONTENT_DIR, f);\n  if (fs.statSync(fullPath).isDirectory()) {\n    fs.readdirSync(fullPath).forEach(sf => {\n      allFiles.push(f + '/' + sf);\n    });\n  } else {\n    allFiles.push(f);\n  }\n});\nconsole.log('All files:', allFiles);\nconsole.log('Slugs:', allFiles.map(f => f.replace(/\\\\.(mdx|md)$/, '')));\n\" 2>&1","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":104,"output":347,"cacheRead":154555,"cacheWrite":299,"totalTokens":155305,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776582974823,"responseId":"0633b4402ba0c7d889507a34ce37d36c"}}
